&lt;p&gt;   &#8230;for dirty non-active segments only when `log.cleaner.min.compaction.lag.ms` is greater than 0&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;   With `log.cleaner.min.compaction.lag.ms`&apos;s default value of 0, there is no need to hold heap objects for those dirty non-active segments. This could reduce the heap size and also avoid the unnecessary monitor lock retrieval.&lt;/p&gt;

